content: This appears to be an order passed by a court, specifically the Supreme Court of India. The order is in response to criminal appeals filed against a judgment passed by a lower court in Uttar Pradesh. The court has allowed part of the appeal and reduced the penalty imposed on the sureties in the case.
Based on the context provided, we can see that the appellants are "Jati Ram & Ors. etc."
Mr. Goyal does not press the appeal in respect of law point on which the High Court had issued a certificate of fitness for appeal to this Court. Therefore, the answer is none of the above.
